crash_tag.var_desc: Unique tag of the crash dataset

party_tag.var_desc: Unique tag of the party dataset

victim_tag.var_desc: Unique tag of the victim dataset

party_number.var_desc: A number that together with the Case ID uniquely identifies a party in a crash

victim_number.var_desc: A number that together with the Case ID uniquely identifies a victim in a crash

crashes_case_tag.var_desc: Total number of crashes per case

parties_case_tag.var_desc: Total number of parties per case

victims_case_tag.var_desc: Total number of victims per case

crashes_ind.var_desc: Indicator variable for the unique crashes in the dataset

parties_ind.var_desc: Indicator variable for the unique parties in the dataset

victims_ind.var_desc: Indicator variable for the unique victims in the dataset

crashes_cid_count.var_desc: Total number of collisions in the crashes dataset

parties_cid_count.var_desc: Total number of collisions in the parties dataset

victims_cid_count.var_desc: Total number of collisions in the victims dataset

parties_pid_count.var_desc: Total number of parties in the parties dataset

victims_pid_count.var_desc: Total number of parties in the victims dataset

victims_vid_count.var_desc: Total number of victims in the victims dataset

date_datetime.var_desc: Date and time of the crash case
date_datetime.notes: Generated by lubridate: as.POSIXlt(paste(crashes$coll_date, crashes$coll_time_temp}, format: '%Y-%m-%d %H:%M', tz: 'America/Los_Angeles')

date_year.var_desc: First day of the year of the crash case

date_quarter.var_desc: First day of the quarter of the crash case

date_month.var_desc: First day of the month of the crash case

date_week.var_desc: First day of the week of the crash case

date_process.notes: Generated by lubridate: as.POSIXlt(crashes$process_date, format: '%Y-%m-%d', tz: 'America/Los_Angeles')

dt_year_week.var_desc: Year week of the crash case

dt_month_day.var_desc: Month day of the crash case

dt_year_day.var_desc: Year day of the crash case

dt_dst.var_desc: Daylight saving time of the crash case

dt_zone.var_desc: Time zone of the crash case

coll_date.var_desc: Collision date reported and recorded at the scene of the accident

coll_time.var_desc: The time when the crash occurred in 24h format

accident_year.var_desc: The year when the crash occurred

process_date.var_desc: The date that the crash case was last changed

rush_hours.var_desc: Rush hours interval ranges (Mon-Fri mornings and evenings)

coll_severity.var_desc: The worst injury suffered by any victim in the crash

coll_severity_num.var_desc: Numeric representation of the worst injury suffered by any victim in the crash

coll_severity_hs.var_desc: Reclassified collision severity for hot spot analysis

coll_severity_bin.var_desc: Binary classification of the worst injury suffered by any victim in the crash

coll_severity_rank.var_desc: Ranked crash severity based on the worst injury suffered by any victim in the crash

coll_severity_rank_num.var_desc: Numeric representation of the ranked crash severity based on the worst injury suffered by any victim in the crash

ind_severe.var_desc: Reclassified indicator variable from severity level where there exist severe injuries in the accident

ind_fatal.var_desc: Reclassified indicator variable from severity level where there exist fatal injuries in the accident

ind_multi.var_desc: Reclassified indicator variable from severity level where there exist multiple injuries or fatalities in the accident

party_count.var_desc: Total number of parties involved in the crash

victim_count.var_desc: Total number of victims involved in the crash

count_severe_inj.var_desc: Number of victims in the crash with suspected serous injury or severe injury

count_visible_inj.var_desc: Number of victims in the crash with suspected minor injury or visible injury

count_complaint_pain.var_desc: Number of victims in the crash with possible injury or complaint of pain

count_fatal_severe.var_desc: Number of victims in the crash with fatal or severe injury

count_minor_pain.var_desc: Number of victims in the crash with minor injury or complaint of pain

count_car_killed.var_desc: Number of killed car victims (drivers or passengers)

count_car_inj.var_desc: Number of injured car victims (drivers or passengers)

primary_coll_factor.var_desc: The primary collision factor that caused the crash

type_of_coll.var_desc: The general type of crash as determined by the first injury or damage-causing event

ped_accident.var_desc: Indicates whether the crash involved a pedestrian

bic_accident.var_desc: Indicates whether the crash involved a bicycle

mc_accident.var_desc: Indicates whether the crash involved a motorcycle

truck_accident.var_desc: Indicates whether the crash involved a big truck

hit_and_run.var_desc: A flag to indicate the severity of hit-and-run crash. Felony hit-and-run resulted in injury or death to other parties. Misdemeanor hit-and-run did not result in injury or death to other parties

hit_and_run_bin.var_desc: Whether the accident involved hit and run (recoded)

alcohol_involved.var_desc: Indicates whether the crash involved a party that had been drinking. Note - a passenger does not count as a party

juris.var_desc: Law enforcement agency that has jurisdiction over the crash

officer_id.var_desc: The badge number of the officer who wrote the crash report

reporting_district.var_desc: Reporting District on the crash report

chp_shift.var_desc: CHP shift at the time of the crash

cnty_city_loc.var_desc: The city or unincorporated county where the crash occurred

special_cond.var_desc: A computed value. O means not private property

labels.5: Vista Point or Rest Area or Sales or Inspection Facility

beat_type.var_desc: Location of crash based on beat

labels.7: Vista Point or Rest Area or Scales or Inspection Facility

chp_beat_type.var_desc: Location of crash based on CHP beat

chp_beat_class.var_desc: Location of crash based on CHP beat class

beat_number.var_desc: Beat of the officer who reported the crash

primary_rd.var_desc: The name of the roadway on which the crash occurred

secondary_rd.var_desc: The name of the roadway that intersects the primary roadway

distance.var_desc: Distance of the crash from the intersection with the secondary roadway in ft

direction.var_desc: Direction of travel of the primary party

intersection.var_desc: A flag that denotes if the crash occurred at the intersection with the secondary roadway
intersection.notes: Aggregation only if the intersection is 1 (Yes)

weather_1.var_desc: Weather condition at the time of the crash

weather_2.var_desc: Additional weather condition at the time of the crash

weather_comb.var_desc: Combined Weather Conditions from WEATHER_1 and WEATHER_2 fields in numeric codes by weather conditions severity

road_surface.var_desc: Roadway surface condition at the time of the crash in the traffic lane(s) involved

road_cond_1.var_desc: Roadway condition at the time of the crash in the traffic lane(s) involved

road_cond_2.var_desc: Second roadway condition at the time of the crash in the traffic lane(s) involved

lighting.var_desc: Lighting conditions at the crash location and the time of the crash

control_device.var_desc: Presence and condition of crash related traffic control devices at the time of the crash. Control devices include regulatory, warning, and construction sings. This excludes striping and officers or other persons directing traffic
control_device.notes: aggregate if the control device is 2 (Not Functioning) or 3 (Obscured)

state_hwy_ind.var_desc: A flag to indicate whether the crash is on or near a state highway
state_hwy_ind.notes: aggregate if the state highway indicator is 1 (State Highway)

side_of_hwy.var_desc: Code provided by Caltrans Coders, applies to divided highway, based on nominal direction of route, for single vehicle is same as nominal direction of travel, overruled by impact with second vehicle after crossing median

tow_away.var_desc: A flag to indicate whether the vehicle was towed away from the crash scene
tow_away.notes: aggregate if the tow away indicator is 1 (Yes)

pcf_code_of_viol.var_desc: he law code that was violated and was the primary cause of the crash

pcf_viol_category.var_desc: A value computed from the law section that was given as the primary cause of the crash

labels.1: Driving or Bicycling Under the Influence of Alcohol or Drug
labels.23: Pedestrian or 'Other' Under the Influence of Alcohol or Drug

pcf_violation.var_desc: The law section given as the primary cause of the crash. The subsection is in the data element pcf_viol_subsection

mviw.var_desc: Describes what, in conjunction with a motor vehicle in-transport, produced the first injury or damage-causing event, on or off the road

point_y.var_desc: The latitude of the geocoded location, uses the World Geodetic System from 1984 (WGS84). POINT_X and POINT_Y are generated using the geociding process by UC Berkeley Safe TREC
